  "text": "Also, an approach was proposed to derive local choreographies (interface processes) from UMM global choreographies to register them in a global repository [CITATION_1] . A UML Profile is proposed to represent local choreographies. It is not based on a model-driven approach. In addition, in this work we use the BPMN standard language so that enterprises can understand and define interface processes, instead of using a particular language.",
